Preheat the oven to 240C/220C Fan/Gas 9. Line a baking tray with baking paper.Mix the sprouts with the oil and pinch of salt in a large bowl. Spread out on the baking tray and roast for 10 minutes, or until the sprouts are golden brown but still crunchy.Meanwhile, lightly crush the caraway seeds with a pestle and mortar. Add the black garlic and thyme and crush to form a rough paste.Heat the butter in a large sauté pan over a medium–high heat. Cook for 3 minutes, until melted and dark brown. Add the crushed garlic paste, sprouts, pumpkin seeds and a pinch of salt. Stir for 30 seconds and then take off the heat. Stir in the lemon juice and transfer to a serving bowl or individual plates. Drizzle over the tahini and serve immediately.